            <div id="application_man">
                <h1>How to use the IOS App</h1>
                <h2>Login Screen</h2>
                <p>
                    This screen is starting point for the application. Here user's can login to their account that they 
                    created through our website. Enter your username in the upper textfield and your password in the lower 
                    textfield. If your username and password are correct then you will advance to the garden selection screen. 
                    If either are incorrect an alert will appear with information on what went wrong.
                </p>
                <img src="login_screenshot.png" alt="login_screen">
                <h2>Garden Selection Screen</h2>
                <p>
                    On this screen you will see all of your gardens you have created in a table format. To select a garden, 
                    simply tap the row with the name of the garden you wish to select. To create a new garden, tap the "+" 
                    symbol in the upper right corner of the screen and you will be taken to a new screen. The user can also 
                    logout by tapping the "logout" button in the upper left corner of the screen.
                </p>
                <img src="garden_select_screenshot.png" alt="garden_select_screen">
                <h2>Create Garden Screen</h2>
                <p>
                    On this screen the user can create a new garden. To create the garden enter the name in the textfield 
                    in the middle of the screen and then tap the "save" button in the upper right corner of the screen. Then 
                    the garden will be created the the user will be taken back to the garden selection screen with the new 
                    garden appended as a new row in the bottom of the list. If the user changes their mind, tap the "cancel" 
                    button and the user will be taken back to the garden selection screen.
                </p>
                <img src="new_garden_screenshot.png" alt="new_garden_screen">
                <h2>Garden Tab</h2>
                <p>
                    This tab is the default view when the application is launched. Refer to the picture below for this
                    section. It shows the
                    title that is set for the plant currently in the garden centered at the top of the screen. Shown
                    underneath
                    the title is the garden’s current temperature, humidity, and when the last time the garden was
                    watered. At
                    the bottom of the screen, there is a button titled “Garden Details”. This button will take you to a
                    screen
                    that displays how much water and electricity the garden has used that day.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot1.png" alt="garden_tab">
                <h2>Search Tab</h2>
                <p>
                    This tab displays the garden’s database entries that are between the two dates in the text fields
                    at the top of the screen.
                    Refer to the picture below for this section. When each text field is tapped, a date picker wheel
                    appears.
                    Simply select the start date in the left text field, and the end date in the right text field. The
                    application
                    will connect to the server and display all the garden’s database entries between the start and end
                    date.
                    When you tap on an entry, you will be taken to the “Garden Details” screen, mentioned in the
                    “Garden Tab”
                    section of this manual, except the data will be for that database entry.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot2.png" alt="search_tab">
                <h2>Settings Tab</h2>
                <p>
                    This tab has three buttons on the screen: Select the data you want recorded, Set a water schedule,
                    Create a water schedule.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot3.png" alt="settings_tab">
                <p>
                    The “Select the data you want recorded” button brings you to the screen shown below. Each entry in
                    the table has a switch
                    on the right side to turn it on or off. When the switch is flipped to the right, with the green
                    showing on
                    the left side of the switch, it is considered on. When the switch is on, that setting is being
                    recorded to
                    the database from your garden daily. When the switch is off, that setting is not being recorded
                    from your
                    garden.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot4.png" alt="settings_2">
                <p>
                    The “Set a water schedule” button brings you to the screen that is shown below. The water schedules
                    you have created are
                    shown here in a table view. Each schedule has a switch on the right of the title of it. Only one
                    schedule
                    may be active at a time so only one switch can be in the on position at a time. To switch to a
                    different
                    schedule simply tap the switch of the schedule you want to set and it will turn on and switch to
                    that schedule.
                    If you tap on one of the schedules it will bring you to the screen described in “Create a water
                    schedule”.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot5.png" alt="settings_3">
                <p>
                    The “Create a water schedule” button brings you to the screen that is shown below. In this screen
                    you set the name of the
                    schedule, starting time for watering, duration of watering, and how often you want the watering to
                    repeat. The app offers the date picker wheel and duration wheel to choose starting and duration time respectively. 
                    Tapping the “Save” button, upper right corner of the screen, will save the schedule and set it to
                    your current
                    watering schedule then bring you back to the “Settings Tab” screen.
                </p>
                <img src="screenshot6.png" alt="settings_4">
                <img src="screenSetting1.png" alt="settings_5">
                <img src="screenSetting2.png" alt="settings_6">
