                    You will be presented with an empty page of where your plants will appear. Here you will be able to
                    manage your plants by opening a page to view the plant logs or
                    to change the plants watering schedules.
                </p>
                <img src="/web_manual/5.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="create plant" width="750" height="500" style="margin:25px 0px">
                <p>
                    <br>
                    To create a new plant in this garden, click <button class="btn btn-info btn-sm">Create Plant</button>
                    and give your new plant
                    a name.
                    <br>
                    Your new plant will appear in the garden. Then you can click on <button class="btn btn-info btn-sm">Settings</button>
                    and it will open the schedules and logs page for the plant selected.
                </p>
                <img src="/web_manual/6.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="plants" width="750" height="500" style="margin:25px 0px">
                <h3>Schedule and Logs</h3>
                <p>
                    In the Schedule & Log page you will see two separate sections to view the logs of the plant and
                    the schedules that you have created.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    In the schedules pane, you will be able to create a new watering schedule that you would like to
                    test out on the plant. You will
                    have the option of watering the plant twice a day and you can set the duration of the watering.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    You will also be able to select which watering schedule should be the default. This is to help you
                    save schedules that worked for you in
                    the past, when you want to test out a new watering technique. You can also use this feature to have
                    preset watering schedules for fall, winter, spring
                    and summer.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    To create a new watering schedule click on <button class="btn btn-info btn-sm">Create Schedule</button>
                    and give your new schedule a name.
                </p>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/web_manual/7.jpg" alt="create schedule" class="img-fluid" width="750" height="500" style="margin:25px 0px">
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/web_manual/8.jpg" alt="create new schedule" class="img-fluid" width="750" height="500"
                        style="margin:25px 0px">
                </figure>
                <p>
                    When the new modal pops up, you will be able to set the start time of the watering and the duration. If you would like 
                    to repeat the watering again that same day then select the checkbox.
                </p>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/web_manual/9.PNG" alt="create new schedule" class="img-fluid" width="750" height="500"
                        style="margin:25px 0px">
                </figure>
                <p>
                    The second start time dialog will be displayed so you can set the second watering time. Once you are done, click create and your watering schedules 
                    will be displayed in the Schedules & Logs page along with any logs that the Arduino board sends to the server.
                </p>
                <figure>
                    <img src="/web_manual/last.PNG" alt="create new schedule" class="img-fluid" width="750" height="500"
                        style="margin:25px 0px">
                </figure>
